President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Kansas and has ordered Federal assistance to help with recovery efforts in areas affected by severe storms, straight-line winds, and flooding from October 4 to October 15, 2018. The Federal funding will be available for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in various counties. It will also be available for statewide hazard mitigation measures. Constance C. Johnson-Cage has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future if requested by the State and based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.